  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Deborah Weston tells about seeing Mary Gray Chapman, who was very nervous and irritable. Mary Gray Chapman &quot;was very thankful to be rid of you, but it hadn&apos;t done her the good she expected.&quot; Joseph Ricketson told Deborah that he had spoken to Sumner about [Henry] Willey, editor of the New Bedford Star, for whom he wished to obtain a post as secretary of the legation. Deborah mentions the death of Judge [Lemuel] Shaw. She concludes the letter by asking: &quot;I wonder if anybody will dare to Med.&quot;</subfield>
